p :::s2:::The dandelion wine that he makes with his ten year old brother Tom and his grandfather represents that beauty .
p :::s12:::He has already discovered that adults and children are two different races , and he lets Tom in on his plan to record the summer .
p :::s18:::Along with their mother , grandmother , and great-grandmother , Douglas and Tom help beat the dust and dirt out of the huge rugs from the house .
p :::s19:::Tom discovers that old people were never children , and he relays this to Douglas .
p :::s30:::This episode ends in comic disaster , and Tom relays it all to Douglas , who is enthralled with the idea of magic .
:::s38:::His brother Tom tries to explain that the romance was happy because it was all they could ever have , but Douglas is not satisfied .
:::s43:::While Tom convinces Charlie that the man killed could not have been the Lonely One because he did not look like the Lonely One they imagined , Douglas is shocked by how close he was to death .
